A
male pedestrian was fatally run over and dragged by a minibus taxi in Pretoria
on Monday night. The
Netcare 911 spokesperson Shawn Herbst said this incident happened at the corner
of 24th Avenue and Nico Smith Avenue in Villeria, in Pretoria. “This
man was fatally run over by a minibus taxi and dragged for a distance,” said
Herbst.  Herbst
said the man was crossing the road at about 8pm. “Paramedics
assessed the adult male and found that he had sustained fatal injuries and was
declared deceased on the scene,” he added. Police
said this case is under investigation. 